<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTERNERS TO ADVISE E. EUROPE EDITORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PARIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
East European editors, long used to being told what to write by Communist 
governments, will get advice on how to break old news habits at a conference 
with Western media heads in Paris next month. 
</P>
<P>
The U.N. Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization said in a statement 
Tuesday that it had arranged the Feb. 27-28 meeting at the request of "several 
international media organizations." 
</P>
<P>
The agency said media executives from 15 Western countries, including the 
United States, are being invited to the conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
