<P>
POLICE BLOCK 1,000 IN CRICKET MARCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police used batons, rubber bullets and tear gas to prevent 1,000 blacks from 
marching on a stadium in Bloemfontein to protest a boycott-breaking English 
cricket team's match with a South African university team. Police said 45 were 
arrested. But another protest of the same match by 500 demonstrators, 
coordinated by black activists and tour organizers, went off without incident. 
</P>
