<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 CLUSTER ROCKETS HIT KABUL; 2 KILLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
KABUL, Afghanistan 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two rebel cluster rockets hit Kabul for the second straight day Tuesday, 
killing two civilians and wounding 28 others, Afghan government spokesman 
Mohammed Naqib said. 
</P>
<P>
Two rockets hit Kabul on Monday but caused no casualties. 
</P>
<P>
Naqib said all four were cluster bomb rockets supplied to guerrillas by the 
United States. The rockets are designed to explode in mid-air, scattering 
scores of different kinds of bombs. In the last three weeks, guerrillas have 
used mostly cluster rockets against Kabul instead of the usual Saker rockets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
