<P>
5 SMALL QUAKES RATTLE DESERT CITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Five small earthquakes struck near this Southern California desert city within 
two hours, seismologists reported. 
</P>
<P>
None of the temblors registered higher than magnitude 2.9, a spokesman for the 
Caltech seismology lab in Pasadena said. The epicenter was 25 miles north of 
town, near the Salton Sea, the spokesman said. The quakes occurred in the 
Brawley seismic zone, a complex web of faults. Seismologists reported similar 
waves of small quakes have struck the region before. 
</P>
</TEXT>
