<P>
TOXIC DUMP OWNER WILL PAY $6 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Operators of a hazardous waste dump alongside San Pablo Bay in Contra Costa 
County have agreed to pay more than $6 million to complete closure of the site, 
state officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Thousands of drums of refinery wastes, pesticides and other dangerous 
substances have been collected at the West Contra Costa County Sanitary 
Landfill in Richmond, officials said. The site was operated as a waste dump 
from 1952 to 1987. In a suit filed last fall, the state accused the operator, 
Richmond Sanitary Service, of failing to get the required approval from the 
state Health Services Department for its closure plan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
