<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: WOMAN WALKING ON STREET IS KIDNAPED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Newhall woman was forced into a car and kidnaped, apparently by a man who was 
romantically interested in her, the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department 
reported Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Marixa Sandoval Mendez, 20, was kidnaped about 6:30 p.m. Monday by Nery Oswaldo 
Lopez, 26, of Newhall, who pulled alongside her as she walked on Arch Street 
toward 6th Street in Newhall, Deputy Dean Scoville said. 
</P>
<P>
Mendez's mother, who was walking about 150 feet behind the young woman, told 
deputies the man abducted her daughter in a maroon 1980 Honda, Scoville said. 
</P>
<P>
Scoville said Mendez, a Guatemalan, has lived in the United States for less 
than a month. He said Lopez told her brother he was attracted to her, but 
family members told deputies the two had no relationship. 
</P>
<P>
Deputies described Lopez as 5 feet, 4 inches tall and 165 pounds, with black 
hair and brown eyes. Mendez was described as 5 feet, 4 inches tall and 110 
pounds, with reddish-brown hair and brown eyes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
