<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: STAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHAUNA SNOW, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
'Follies' Cast: Juliet Prowse and Shani Wallis will play former showgirls, 
Dorothy Lamour will sing "Broadway Baby," and Yma Sumac will warble "One More 
Kiss" in her first "legit" appearance since 1951. 
</P>
<P>
They'll all be in Long Beach Civic Light Opera's staging of Stephen Sondheim's 
"Follies," March 1-18. Other prominent players will include Harvey Evans, Karen 
Morrow, Billy Barnes and Ed Evanko. Evans, who created the role of the younger 
Buddy in the original "Follies" in 1970, this time will play the older Buddy. 
SHAUNA SNOW 
</P>
</TEXT>
