<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISH REPORT: BIG BASS ARE AVAILABLE AT LAKE CASTAIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles County's Lake Castaic continues to be the hot spot for largemouth 
bass, except when high winds close the launch ramp, keeping boats off the lake. 
</P>
<P>
Both the upper and lower reservoirs have been productive. Kevin Morris of Sun 
Valley took a 13-pound 4-ounce bass in the lower lake, and Bob Jones of Canoga 
Park caught an 11-pounder in the upper. 
</P>
</TEXT>
