<DATELINE>
<P>
FULLERTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Fullerton and pitcher Huck Flener opened the baseball season 
impressively, leading the Titans to a 6-1 victory over Cal Poly Pomona in a 
nonconference game Tuesday at Titan Field. 
</P>
<P>
Flener, a junior left-hander, allowed two hits and an unearned run in six 
innings. 
</P>
<P>
Bill Fitzgerald, Rich Faulks and Doug Ketchen each pitched an inning of relief. 
</P>
<P>
Flener, who had four strikeouts, retired the final five batters he faced. 
</P>
<P>
Flener gave credit for his strong outing to his improved changeup. 
</P>
<P>
"It's a lot better than last year," he said. "(Last year) I threw it, but I 
didn't have as much control. Now I can throw it when I'm behind in the count." 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton scored four runs in the second inning. David Ayala and Mate Borgogno 
each had two-run singles. Borgogno added an RBI single in the fourth, giving 
Fullerton a 5-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
The Titans' final run came on Domingo Mota's home run over the left-field 
fence. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton finished with 10 hits, including two each by Borgogno and Ayala. 
</P>
<P>
"We played very well for the first time out," Fullerton Coach Larry Cochell 
said. STEVE KRESAL 
