<TEXT>
<P>
A day after the U.S. State Department expressed concern, Defense Minister 
Yitzhak Rabin ordered a temporary halt to the expulsion of Palestinians living 
in the occupied territories without residency permits, a practice that often 
separates husbands and wives. 
</P>
<P>
Today's announcement cited humanitarian reasons for halting the expulsions, 
which have torn apart hundreds of families in the past year. 
</P>
<P>
Palestinian activists claim the expulsions have been stepped up and are part of 
a long-term strategy to force Palestinians out of the occupied West Bank and 
Gaza Strip, where the Palestinian uprising against Israeli authority has 
claimed hundreds of lives over the last 26 months. 
