<P>
Ray Sharkey, who played a mobster on TV's "Wiseguy," hugged and kissed reputed 
crime boss John Gotti at Gotti's assault trial. 
</P>
<P>
Sharkey visited the courtroom Tuesday and the pair later lunched at Giambone's, 
an Italian restaurant, the New York Post reported today. 
</P>
<P>
Sharkey, who said he has known Gotti since they were children in Brooklyn, 
portrayed the fictional crime kingpin Sonny Steelgrave in the TV series. 
Sharkey is researching a movie that deals with the Mafia, his publicist told 
the Post. 
</P>
